# Test Conventions

> Testing standards for {{ project_name | default("this project") }}.

## Test Structure

{% if test_structure %}{{ test_structure }}{% else %}- Tests live alongside source in `tests/` directories or `_test` suffixed files
- Integration tests in dedicated `tests/` at crate/package level
- E2E tests in workspace-level `tests/` directory
{% endif %}

## Naming

- Test files: `{{ test_file_naming | default("<module>_test") }}`
- Test functions: `test_<scenario>` — descriptive, not `test_1`
- Test fixtures: reuse via shared helpers, not copy-paste

## Practices

- Write tests FIRST (TDD: Red -> Green -> Refactor)
- Each test covers ONE behavior
- No test pollution — each test creates its own state
- Mock external dependencies, test real logic
- Test error paths and edge cases, not just happy paths

## Coverage Targets

{% if coverage %}{{ coverage }}{% else %}- Core logic: aim for high coverage
- I/O boundaries: integration tests
- Templates: verify rendered output is valid markdown
{% endif %}

## Test Categories

| Category | Scope | Speed |
|----------|-------|-------|
| Unit | Single function/method | < 10ms |
| Integration | Module/crate boundary | < 100ms |
| E2E | Full system flow | < 5s |
